#DOC source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/17--newsletter-posts.md strip=7% toon=5% net=11%
T|17 ·|0|A full nl studio integrated w/ the Kit ap — compose, ds, broadcast, run sequences/automations, and al cg. The owner is starting a monthly nl as part of the Life OS.
T|17 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|Bring em newsletters into Mission Control. Integrated w/ Kit (formerly ConvertKit) via its ap, it helps al subscribers, compose/write/ds the nl, manage and al cg, and potentially write automations/sequences. The stated near-term goal is a monthly nl.
T|Purp|1|
T|Page|0|Title: nl, breadcrumb Vibe w/ AI / nl.
T|Page|1|Sub-line: "Mission Control → KIT · broadcasts · lifecycle sequences, measured on clicks, replies & conversions."
T|Page|2|Connected to KIT status, Visit workspace, ap healthy, last-sync time.
T|Page|3|Buttons: Open in Kit and New broadcast.
T|Page|4|A note: "Matching powers Vahalla behind the same if."
T|Page|5|
T|Tabs|0|A horizontal tab bar drives the page: Audience, Compose, Broadcasts, Sequences, Growth, an.
T|Tabs|1|
T|Audi|0|Subscriber metrics — total subscribers (e.g. 128) w/ a tn sparkline, new subscribers (+12), unsubscribes (2), etc.
T|Audi|1|By tag / segment breakdown — counts per audience segment: e.g. nl 128, Course waitlist 41, In subscribers / app us 63, Consulting leads, Dormant (90d) 11, etc. — so the owner can target broadcasts to specific segments.
T|Audi|2|
T|Comp|0|A draft editor for the issue. Example issue: #13 "The cockpit, not the dashboard."
T|Comp|1|Subject line field and preview text, w/ the ag proposing options.
T|Comp|2|Block-based body — cn blocks (story summary, links, "By ds — ship while you sleep," CTA) w/ + Add a block.
T|Comp|3|Approval gate explainer — e.g. "Posting a send to KIT … an external action … William can prep the draft + send, [but] schedule/send is gated until you rv." — drafts are prepared but the actual send is gated on the owner.
T|Comp|4|Action buttons: ap & schedule via Kit, ap & send now, Regenerate cp, Send tst to myself.
T|Comp|5|
T|Broa|0|perf of past sends — a list of sent issues w/ open rate, click rate, and counts (e.g. #13 Meet the ag roster, #12 Now I plan w/ no code, #11 The memory architecture), each w/ open/click %.
T|Broa|1|A Top performer callout and a learning note (e.g. "#11 'Meet the ag roster' … X% click rate … Learning note: William [in]; single clear CTA + free feature did best. Lean into narrower ag-centric nx send.").
T|Broa|2|
T|Sequ|0|Visual automation flows: Welcome series, New app feature announce, Cart recapture (abandoned cart), etc., each a multi-step sequence w/ triggers (e.g. "has signed up," "tag applied," "cart abandoned") and timed steps.
T|Sequ|1|Propose sequence — the ag can ds a new sequence ("designed in AI · authored in KIT via the ap").
T|Sequ|2|
T|Grow|0|Sign-up surfaces / what's driving the list — sources feeding subscriber growth: YouTube description link (+9), Course waitlist form (+1), viBweAtti.io landing page, By ds in-app capture, etc., each w/ counts and conversion notes.
T|Grow|1|
T|an|0|cg an: opens, clicks, replies, conversions over time and by cg, to "manage and al the different cg."
T|an|1|
T|Righ|0|A live em preview of the current issue branded to the workspace ("Vibe w/ AI"), e.g. "I stopped building dashboards…" w/ a Try in [Kit] CTA — a WYSIWYG of what subscribers receive.
T|Righ|1|
T|Agen|0|William drafts/composes; the ag designs sequences and proposes cp.
T|Agen|1|All sending flows through the Kit ap; the send action is human-gated until trust is built (consistent w/ the em/sl draft-first pattern).